Located in the city of Makkah, Saudi Arabia, Jabal Omar Development is a multi-use real estate mega development project that is within reasonable walking distance of the Grand Mosque of Makkah. The city is where visitors and Muslim pilgrims often come in search of harmony and peace. The project blends innovation and tradition through the choice to preserve the Islamic architectural style with the infusion of modern design. Its main aim is to offer a luxurious atmosphere as well as a distinctive design that makes guests feel at peace, comfort, and tranquility. Also Read: Financial Close Attained For Red Sea Multi-Utilities Project in Saudi Arabia It includes the constriction of 40 towers located on top of the 16 structural bases with a total built-in area of well over two million square meters. The towers will consist of an array of apartments, malls, hotels as well as residential units. When completed and in full operation, the project will also include various five-star and four-star hotels. The hotels are projected to be within the capacity to host up to well over 36,000 annually and express a sharp spike in excess during the Hajj season of well over 100,000 guests. Briefly described, the Jabal Omar Development is a monumental cluster of hotel-operated units and apartments that are open to investment from interested and potential buyers. Since the project neighbors the Grand mosque, a part of the Jabal Omar hotelâ€™s goals involves providing true hospitality as it is not just an important arabinan virtue but also an attribute and display of good faith. The project was conceived after Jabal Omar Development Company signed an SR 1.6 billion, translating to an approximately US$ 426M financing deal. The project includes four towers that have got 2,160 rooms and a total commercial area of 26,435 square meters.